TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {42784=+1 212 318 2000, 4915=Phone: 613-691-1091, 42452=+65 6212 1000, 4515=Focus Graphite Inc., a junior mining development company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties primarily in Québec, Canada. It primarily explores for graphite, rare earth elements, copper, nickel, platinum, palladium, and base metal deposits. The company owns interests in the Lac Knife graphite deposit that comprises 57 map-designated claims covering 2,986.31 hectares and is located to the south-southwest of Fermont town, Côte-Nord region. It also has interests in the Kwyjibo polymetallic Iron-Rare Earth Elements-Copper-(Gold) property, which consists of 118 map-designated claims covering 6,278 hectares and is located to the northeast of Sept-Îles, Côte-Nord administrative district; and the Romer & Labrador Trough project that comprises 13 properties covering approximately 668 square kilometers and is located in Quebec. The company was formerly known as Focus Metals Inc. and changed its name to Focus Graphite Inc. in May 2012. The company was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Ottawa, Canada.}
